---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Uses">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[68ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-none">
        Uses
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed">
        I optimize for tools that disappear into the background. I prefer software that reduces friction instead of adding features.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Decisions and Workflows -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-10 text-[#FAFAFA] text-sm leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      
      <!-- Writing -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold font-mono">Writing</h2>
        <p class="text-[#A1A1AA]">
          <strong class="text-white font-medium">Why I write in Markdown.</strong> 
          Writing in plain text guarantees absolute content longevity. Word processors and proprietary databases create vendor lock-in. Markdown files can be searched, compiled, and read on any system fifty years from now.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Development -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold font-mono">Development</h2>
        <p class="text-[#A1A1AA]">
          <strong class="text-white font-medium">Why I prefer simple tooling.</strong> 
          Complex configurations introduce subtle breakages. I favor terminal tools and minimal environments because they reduce the surface area of potential friction. If an editor requires more than a few lines of configuration to be usable, it is too complex.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Learning -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold font-mono">Learning</h2>
        <p class="text-[#A1A1AA]">
          <strong class="text-white font-medium">Why I study from primary sources.</strong> 
          Tutorials summarize another person's understanding, which frequently filters out essential edge cases. Reading the raw RFCs, system documentation, and specifications reveals the actual trade-offs that designers struggled with.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Reading -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold font-mono">Reading</h2>
        <p class="text-[#A1A1AA]">
          <strong class="text-white font-medium">How I annotate books.</strong> 
          Passive reading leaves little lasting trace. I read physical copies or static PDFs, writing summaries, margins arguments, and systems structures diagrams inside my notes for every chapter finished.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Planning -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold font-mono">Planning</h2>
        <p class="text-[#A1A1AA]">
          <strong class="text-white font-medium">Why I keep plans lightweight.</strong> 
          Detailed long-term charts rarely survive contact with real-world requirements. I structure tasks in simple, text-based checklists that cover only immediate, actionable goals for the current development cycles.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Research -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold font-mono">Research</h2>
        <p class="text-[#A1A1AA]">
          <strong class="text-white font-medium">How I validate ideas.</strong> 
          Before writing code, I compile a system architecture model, mapping database constraints and request sequences. Only when the data states transition predictably do I begin writing source code.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Software & Hardware specifications (Muted at the bottom) -->
      <section class="border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pt-8 mt-4 flex flex-col gap-4 text-xs font-mono text-[#71717A]">
        <h3 class="text-[10px] uppercase font-semibold text-white tracking-wider">The Stack</h3>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <div>Hardware: <span class="text-[#A1A1AA]">LOQ Ryzen 7, Xiaomi Pad 5, Realme 12 Pro</span></div>
          <div>Editor & Term: <span class="text-[#A1A1AA]">Cursor / Neovim, Warp Terminal</span></div>
          <div>Security: <span class="text-[#A1A1AA]">1Password, GnuPG commit signing keys</span></div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
